ture.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Storage is intentionally simple: a flat JSON index plus one file per document is enough at small scale. Beyond a few thousand documents this becomes the bottleneck and should be replaced with SQLite or a proper document store. Flat files are easy to inspect for debugging."}, {"id": "raw_architecture_keyword_overlap_threshold", "label": "Keyword Overlap Threshold", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "raw/architecture.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Cross-reference detection is intentionally naive: keyword overlap of three is reasonable for short documents but produces too many false positives on long ones. A real system would use TF-IDF or embedding similarity instead."}], "edges": [{"source": "raw_architecture_document_pipeline", "target": "raw_architecture_parsing_stage", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "raw/architecture.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "raw_architecture_document_pipeline", "target": "raw_architecture_validation_stage", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "raw/architecture.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "raw_architecture_document_pipeline", "target": "raw_architecture_processing_stage", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "raw/architecture.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "raw_architecture_document_pipeline", "target": "raw_architecture_storage_stage", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "raw/architecture.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "raw_architecture